Speaker of the House of Representatives, Femi Gbajabiamila, has described as worrisome reports that about 10.5 million children are out of school in Nigeria. He stated this during the flag-off of the enrolment of 500 children in schools, as well as a free medical outreach to 10,000 residents in Zamfara State. Also Read:Â Design Your Curriculum To Reflect 21st-Century Reality, Osinbajo Tells WAEC The Speaker who was represented by his Chief of Staff, Garba Rikiji, described as unacceptable the alarming rate of out-of-school children in the country. He explained that it is a time bomb that leaders and concerned citizens must join hands together to address before it explodes.